  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "TensorFlow is an end-to-end open source platform for machine learning. Passing a complex argument to `tf.transpose` at the same time as passing `conjugate=True` argument results in a crash. The fix will be included in TensorFlow 2.5.0. We will also cherrypick this commit on TensorFlow 2.4.2, TensorFlow 2.3.3, TensorFlow 2.2.3 and TensorFlow 2.1.4, as these are also affected and still in supported range.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2021-29618 describes a crash in TensorFlow's tf.transpose with complex inputs and conjugate=True; it is a vulnerability in a core ML framework used in AI pipelines. It affects commonly used AI software stacks and requires patching across multiple TensorFlow versions, representing a software supply-chain vulnerability in the AI stack. The report provides clear description, affected versions, and references sufficient for AVID curation."
  },
